Computer: From Electronics to Programming


1. Diode
•	• Definition: Allows current to flow in only one direction.
•	• Types: Silicon, Zener, Schottky, LED.
•	• Applications: Rectification and reverse-polarity protection.
•	• Exercise: Design a half-wave rectifier circuit.
2. Transistors
•	• Types: BJT and MOSFET.
•	• Function: Works as a switch or amplifier.
•	• Exercise: Build a circuit to drive a small DC motor.
3. Logic Gates
•	• Types: AND, OR, NOT, NAND, NOR, XOR, XNOR.
•	• Truth tables.
•	• Examples: Half Adder, Full Adder.
4. Flip-Flops
•	• Types: SR, JK, D, T.
•	• Application: Build a binary counter.
5. CPU (Central Processing Unit)
•	• Components: ALU, Control Unit, Registers.
•	• Instruction Cycle: Fetch-Decode-Execute.
6. RAM (Main Memory)
•	• Types: SRAM, DRAM, Cache.
•	• Memory hierarchy.
7. Binary System
•	• Number conversions.
•	• Two’s complement, IEEE‑754 floating‑point format.
8. Machine Language
•	• Binary instructions.
•	• Examples: LOAD, ADD, JMP.
9. Assembly Language
•	• Registers, instructions, labels.
•	• Practical example.
10. C Language
•	• Pointers, memory management.
•	• Simple practical project.
